What you need to know:

Peter Gachoka and Lucy Maina won the longest drive. A field of 207 players participated in the event, where a Toyota Corola was stake for a hole in one and Anastacia Karimi was the closest, though she could only take home the nearest to pin award.At the par 73 Kitale Golf Club, John Thuo carded 70 nett in the first round and an excellent 66 in the second round for a total of 136 nett. He beat Patrice Tomno (68, 68) on countback, while Kevin Nyaga on 137 nett beat Kakamega’s J. Akhonya on countback to finish third. 